QIIME 2 is one of the most widely used platforms for microbiome data analysis, especially for 16S rRNA gene amplicon sequencing, shotgun metagenomics, and ITS fungal data.

1. Set up QIIME 2
Install QIIME 2 in a conda environment:
wget https://data.qiime2.org/distro/core/qiime2-2025.2-py39-linux-conda.yml
conda env create -n qiime2-2025.2 --file qiime2-2025.2-py39-linux-conda.yml
conda activate qiime2-2025.2

# Confirm installation:
qiime --help

2. Import Your Data
QIIME 2 uses .qza (artifacts) and .qzv (visualizations) as its file formats.

qiime tools import \
  --type 'SampleData[PairedEndSequencesWithQuality]' \
  --input-path manifest.csv \
  --output-path demux-paired-end.qza \
  --input-format PairedEndFastqManifestPhred33V2

3. Quality Control & Denoising
Denoising removes sequencing errors and produces amplicon sequence variants (ASVs).

qiime dada2 denoise-paired \
  --i-demultiplexed-seqs demux-paired-end.qza \
  --p-trunc-len-f 240 \
  --p-trunc-len-r 200 \
  --o-table table.qza \
  --o-representative-sequences rep-seqs.qza \
  --o-denoising-stats denoising-stats.qza

** You choose --p-trunc-len values based on your quality plot.

4. Assign Taxonomy
Download a pre-trained classifier (e.g., SILVA, Greengenes) and run:
qiime feature-classifier classify-sklearn \
  --i-classifier silva-138-99-nb-classifier.qza \
  --i-reads rep-seqs.qza \
  --o-classification taxonomy.qza

Visualize:
qiime metadata tabulate \
  --m-input-file taxonomy.qza \
  --o-visualization taxonomy.qzv

5. Create Phylogenetic Tree
qiime phylogeny align-to-tree-mafft-fasttree \
  --i-sequences rep-seqs.qza \
  --o-alignment aligned-rep-seqs.qza \
  --o-masked-alignment masked-aligned-rep-seqs.qza \
  --o-tree unrooted-tree.qza \
  --o-rooted-tree rooted-tree.qza

6. Diversity Analysis
qiime diversity core-metrics-phylogenetic \
  --i-phylogeny rooted-tree.qza \
  --i-table table.qza \
  --p-sampling-depth 10000 \
  --m-metadata-file sample-metadata.tsv \
  --output-dir core-metrics-results

This produces:
Alpha diversity (Shannon, Observed ASVs, Faithâ€™s PD)
Beta diversity (PCoA plots of UniFrac and Bray-Curtis distances)

7. Differential Abundance (Optional)
For group comparisons:
qiime diversity alpha-group-significance \
  --i-alpha-diversity core-metrics-results/shannon_vector.qza \
  --m-metadata-file sample-metadata.tsv \
  --o-visualization core-metrics-results/shannon-group-significance.qzv
You can also use ANCOM for taxa-level differential abundance.

8. Export & Visualize
To view .qzv files:
qiime tools view taxonomy.qzv
Or use https://view.qiime2.org
Export data for external plotting:
qiime tools export --input-path table.qza --output-path exported-table





